messages.message:
Looks like it actually wasn’t blueprint… it was an old style override from before it was moved into the main repo
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/68487
So this has always been like this?? Why has no one caught this before?

No it wasn’t like this before https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/68191
That’s because `SUpsellButtonInDropdown` included styles to override the other style override but it only targeted `button` tags & not `a` tags
